  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help the Shipibo Regenerate from the Pandemic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ASOMASHK, the Shipibo-Konibo Association of Onanyabo (ancestral healers), has developed a treatment and revitalization protocol for Shipibo communities heavily hit by COVID-19. In partnership with Chaikuni Institute and the Temple of the Way of Light, they successfully reached 333 people in 10 communities. And now, also supported by the Shipibo Conibo Center, they aim to reach farther along the Ucayali River to continue their work and develop strategies for long-term care and crisis response.</narrative>
  </description>
